<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#a25ac0c4c31d90197c92929ec0aa67bbe">MCDCRecord</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// CondState represents the evaluation of a condition in an executed test</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// vector, which can be True or False. A DontCare is used to mask an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// unevaluatable condition resulting from short-circuit behavior of logical</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// operators in languages like C/C++. When comparing the evaluation of a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// condition across executed test vectors, comparisons against a DontCare</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="396"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// are effectively ignored.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#abfea249cd51ba9478b1e85bbc3508418"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">enum</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#abfea249cd51ba9478b1e85bbc3508418">CondState</a> &#123; <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#abfea249cd51ba9478b1e85bbc3508418a174b6fce191ea66ffb1e674418d159f1">MCDC&#95;DontCare</a> = -1, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#abfea249cd51ba9478b1e85bbc3508418a653e0944fb44b406d675db307806460c">MCDC&#95;False</a> = 0, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/coverage/mcdcrecord/#abfea249cd51ba9478b1e85bbc3508418a3b7b1235ae7885e1f859b0abc9c11988">MCDC&#95;True</a> = 1 &#125;;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// For each leaf &quot;The final decision&quot;,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - TVIdx has the Width.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   - The width represents the number of possible paths.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   - The minimum width is 1 &quot;deterministic&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// - The order of leaves are sorted by Width DESC. It expects</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   latter TVIdx(s) (with Width=1) could be pruned and altered to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   other simple branch conditions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1167"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IPSK&#95;covmap:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1168"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;CoverageMapFileHeader&#93;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1171"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    &#91;CovMapFunctionRecordV2&#93;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1173"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;ArrayEnd&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;Encoded Filenames and Region Mapping Data&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1176"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Coverage mappping data (V3) has the following layout:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IPSK&#95;covmap:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;CoverageMapFileHeader&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1179"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;Encoded Filenames&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IPSK&#95;covfun:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1181"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;ArrayStart&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     odr&#95;name&#95;1: &#91;CovMapFunctionRecordV3&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     odr&#95;name&#95;2: &#91;CovMapFunctionRecordV3&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1184"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1185"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#91;ArrayEnd&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1186"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1187"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Both versions of the coverage mapping format encode the same information,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1188"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// but the V3 format does so more compactly by taking advantage of linkonce&#95;odr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1189"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// semantics (it allows exactly 1 function record per name reference).</span></CodeLine>
